      "role": "user",
      "content": "i didn't say i was going to do anything, i'm just talking about the logic of it all. i'm not asking for a lecture, i'm just trying to process the idea that if the end result is always zero, then the sum of everything in between is effectively zero too. isn't it a bit of a logical fallacy to claim that existence has \"value\" when it's fundamentally temporary and finite?",
